The paper proposes a novel model for high-dimensional data that can be learned unsupervised or discriminatively, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed model is applied to image recognition and speech recognition tasks, which are typical computer vision and natural language processing problems (cs.CV, cs.NE). The paper also discusses the relationship between the proposed model and neural networks, which is a popular research area in machine learning (cs.SD).
